# CLI Tooling

- Treat CLI work as Archetype 6 from `docs/architecture/doctrine/06-archetypes.md`.
- Keep command features vertically sliced: command, input, use case, and helpers live together when
  they describe one user-facing command.
- Presentation parses and renders only. Filesystem, process, network, and platform effects belong
  behind injected ports or adapters, as required by `docs/architecture/doctrine/09-anti-patterns-and-fitness-functions.md`.
- Composition roots wire command groups and dependencies; they should reference feature commands
  rather than contain inline command bodies.
- Use `tools/fitness/check-cli-*.ts` gates when available before merging CLI structure changes.
